name: AI Sell
headline: AI Sales Associate for Ecommerce
description:
We're building AI Sales Associates for eCommerce. Imagine going on nike.com and facetiming an AI Lebron James and getting his advice on which his shoes to buy. Traditional brick-and-mortar retail stores rely on sales associates to provide personalized customer service, guide product discovery and close sales, but it's always been too expensive and unscaleable for online stores. We're building video-based AI agents that are experts in their products and can gently steer customers to a purchase, delighting customers and lifting conversion/AOV.

Jerry and Jeffrey are brothers who previously worked together to scale The Coding School to a 6mil+ in revenue. Jerry built software to help run the 50+ Shopify brands that Openstore acquired more profitably and efficiently. He was also an engineer at Flexport and Google.

Jeffrey previously worked at DRW as a quant trader, and as an engineer at Facebook, Snowflake and Amazon.

founders.name: Jerry Liu, Cofounder, CEO
founders.description: CEO/Cofounder @ AI Sell. Excited to build on my work at Openstore where I built software to run 50+ Shopify brands more profitably. Also worked on payments at Flexport and ads at Google. Was CTO of The Coding School, a nonprofit that raised 6m+ from Google/IBM/Department of Defense. CS @ Duke.

generated_description:
**AI Sell: Revolutionizing E-Commerce with AI Sales Associates**

AI Sell is an innovative startup with a clear mission: to create AI Sales Associates specifically designed for eCommerce. Imagine visiting a site like Nike.com and having the chance to FaceTime with an AI version of LeBron James for personalized shoe advice. This vision reflects the core of AI Sell’s approach—providing customers with engaging and tailored shopping experiences that traditional brick-and-mortar retailers have long depended on, but in a scalable online format.

Founded in 2024, AI Sell emerged from the minds of brothers Jerry and Jeffrey, who bring a wealth of experience to the table. Previously, they scaled The Coding School to over $6 million in revenue. Jerry, with a solid background in software engineering from places like Flexport and Google, developed tools to help manage multiple Shopify brands for Openstore more effectively. Jeffrey complements this with his experience as a quant trader at DRW and roles at giants such as Facebook, Snowflake, and Amazon. Together, they harness their diverse skills to tackle the challenge of personalized service in eCommerce.

Operating out of San Francisco and currently part of Y Combinator's Batch S24, AI Sell is small but mighty, with a team of just two employees. Their Group Partner is Jared Friedman, who adds invaluable guidance and mentorship.

In an industry where sales and customer experiences are crucial, AI Sell is poised to innovate the way consumers interact with online shopping. By combining video technology with AI expertise, they hope to not just improve conversion rates but also enhance overall customer satisfaction through a delightful shopping journey.

For more information and to keep an eye on their progress, visit their website at [AI Sell](https://www.aisell.com). 

**Tags:** Sales, E-commerce, AI, San Francisco Bay Area.
